The paper discusses the development of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) for safety-critical applications, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ANNs in safety-critical applications also involves system engineering (cs.SY) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) considerations. Additionally, the paper discusses the engineering methods used for hardening ANNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
